WEBVTT

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:12.970
By 2036,

00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:16.100
it will have resulted in 5.7 billion casualties worldwide.

00:00:16.410 --> 00:00:17.680
And this is what starts it.

00:00:18.440 --> 00:00:20.550
Huh? What is it?

00:00:20.550 --> 00:00:22.150
It's only a model.

00:00:22.150 --> 00:00:23.850
Maybe it transforms or something?

00:00:23.850 --> 00:00:25.580
A time machine.

00:00:26.090 --> 00:00:27.390
Seriously?

00:00:27.650 --> 00:00:31.090
I knew you'd recognize it, Uncle.

00:00:31.090 --> 00:00:32.720
Then that makes this easy.

00:00:33.350 --> 00:00:35.180
Come with me.

00:00:39.610 --> 00:00:41.390
I refuse...

00:00:42.090 --> 00:00:43.770
Okarin?

00:00:43.770 --> 00:00:46.560
I've come here from the alpha world line.

00:00:47.270 --> 00:00:48.880
Over the past three weeks,

00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:51.350
I changed that world line again and again,

00:00:51.350 --> 00:00:55.600
sacrificing Kurisu to return here, 
to the beta world line.

00:00:55.600 --> 00:01:00.770
I can't let all of that count for nothing!

00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:03.010
Kurisu-san?

00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:05.460
Kurisu?

00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:08.920
Wasn't that the name of the scientist

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:11.270
who was stabbed at the Radio Building?

00:01:14.420 --> 00:01:15.850
Okabe Rintarou,

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:20.650
what if I told you that the way 
to avoid World War III

00:01:20.650 --> 00:01:23.770
is to prevent Makise Kurisu's death

00:01:23.770 --> 00:01:27.020
on July 28th, 2010?

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:31.020
What do you mean?

00:01:31.020 --> 00:01:33.340
I don't know the details.

00:01:33.340 --> 00:01:36.520
But I have one mission...

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:38.540
To save Makise Kurisu,

00:01:38.540 --> 00:01:42.680
and to go to the one world line unaffected 
by the Attractor Field:

00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:45.890
The Steins Gate!

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:53.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:03:15.790 --> 00:03:20.770
Open the Steins Gate

00:03:22.070 --> 00:03:24.340
Steins Gate?

00:03:24.340 --> 00:03:26.550
The architects of this plan were

00:03:26.550 --> 00:03:29.800
my father and your future self.

00:03:30.280 --> 00:03:32.890
None of it is anything more than a hypothesis.

00:03:32.890 --> 00:03:36.320
It's possible the theory is wrong,

00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:40.220
and there is no Steins Gate world line.

00:03:40.430 --> 00:03:43.310
But I'm going anyway.

00:03:43.310 --> 00:03:47.530
I'll bet on the chance that 
a bright future's waiting for me.

00:03:48.100 --> 00:03:51.020
If you're coming with me,

00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:52.930
then take my hand.

00:04:01.060 --> 00:04:02.680
Um,

00:04:02.680 --> 00:04:06.960
Mayushii didn't really understand any of that.

00:04:06.960 --> 00:04:09.500
But if this person,

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:14.550
this Kurisu-san, is important to you,

00:04:15.630 --> 00:04:17.600
shouldn't you try to help them?

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:22.850
World War III sounds too much 
like one of your fantasies.

00:04:22.850 --> 00:04:25.770
No one else could handle it.

00:04:28.470 --> 00:04:31.790
I don't care about 5.7 billion people in the future.

00:04:32.410 --> 00:04:33.770
But...

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:38.390
Thank you.

00:04:40.060 --> 00:04:41.490
Board now.

00:04:41.490 --> 00:04:43.090
Two people can get in it?

00:04:43.090 --> 00:04:44.520
Of course!

00:04:44.520 --> 00:04:48.060
This is my father's masterpiece.

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:53.970
Okarin!

00:04:55.580 --> 00:04:57.520
Leave your phone.

00:04:57.520 --> 00:05:01.310
It might get crossed with your 
phone in the past.

00:05:02.940 --> 00:05:04.250
I'll return.

00:05:08.040 --> 00:05:09.850
Good luck.

00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:12.220
This is a time machine.

00:05:12.220 --> 00:05:12.980
Yeah,

00:05:12.980 --> 00:05:16.720
I stopped in 1975 and 2000.

00:05:16.720 --> 00:05:18.480
It's working fine.

00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:22.220
But it's running out of fuel...

00:05:22.220 --> 00:05:24.640
Wait, it can go from past to future?

00:05:25.750 --> 00:05:27.260
Of course it can.

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:28.430
It's a time machine.

00:05:28.810 --> 00:05:30.640
<i>I see...</i>

00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:33.270
<i>Is that because we're in a different world line now?</i>

00:05:33.270 --> 00:05:34.430
Sit down.

00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:39.100
We'll head to just before noon, on July 28th.

00:05:39.100 --> 00:05:40.910
We can't change location,

00:05:40.910 --> 00:05:43.850
so if we arrive too early, it'll spread 
panic at the Radio Building,

00:05:43.850 --> 00:05:46.680
possibly affecting Makise Kurisu's actions.

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:49.500
Your first time, the Gs are pretty tough.

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:51.020
Get ready.

00:06:01.480 --> 00:06:03.100
Okarin...

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:08.500
What is this?

00:06:08.500 --> 00:06:10.090
These always show up.

00:06:10.090 --> 00:06:11.560
I guess they're like fragments of time.

00:06:11.860 --> 00:06:13.480
Pretty, huh?

00:06:18.850 --> 00:06:20.220
Let's go!

00:06:20.220 --> 00:06:22.070
W-Wait.

00:06:22.070 --> 00:06:24.380
I think I'm going to throw up...

00:06:24.380 --> 00:06:26.500
You're a wimp...

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:27.470
Hurry!

00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:34.640
Don't let your other self encounter you.

00:06:34.640 --> 00:06:37.260
It'll cause a serious time paradox.

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:39.680
How long until her stabbing?

00:06:39.680 --> 00:06:42.390
Twenty minutes or so, I guess.

00:06:42.780 --> 00:06:45.540
I'll ready the time machine.

00:06:45.540 --> 00:06:47.670
You protect her, Uncle.

00:06:47.670 --> 00:06:48.970
Stop calling me that.

00:06:50.600 --> 00:06:52.380
<i>July 28th.</i>

00:06:52.660 --> 00:06:55.660
<i>The day I saw Kurisu lying in a pool of blood,</i>

00:06:55.660 --> 00:06:57.540
<i>I'd come with Mayuri to see</i>

00:06:57.540 --> 00:06:59.720
<i>Professor Nakabachi's press conference.</i>

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:01.840
<i>I heard a noise on the roof.</i>

00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:18.380
<i>That's right. After this, Mayuri goes 
to the 7th-floor Upa machines.</i>

00:07:18.380 --> 00:07:19.820
<i>Oh, no!</i>

00:07:19.820 --> 00:07:22.540
You called me here for this?

00:07:23.060 --> 00:07:26.640
There aren't many left of this series, 
and Mayushii's...

00:07:26.640 --> 00:07:28.180
<i>Oh well.</i>

00:07:28.180 --> 00:07:30.580
<i>I'll take the back stairs to the 8th floor.</i>

00:07:31.530 --> 00:07:34.560
It's a metal... A metal Upa!

00:07:34.560 --> 00:07:35.820
Is it rare?

00:07:35.820 --> 00:07:37.560
Really!

00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:39.890
<i>If I make it here... </i>

00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:44.930
I'm sorry.

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:47.280
K-Kurisu?

00:07:48.480 --> 00:07:49.930
H-How do you know my name?

00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:53.140
<i>Kurisu is alive...</i>

00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:55.560
Have we met somewhere?

00:07:56.460 --> 00:07:57.520
Kurisu...

00:07:57.520 --> 00:07:58.600
Are you listening...

00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:03.350
What's wrong?

00:08:03.350 --> 00:08:05.180
Answer me.

00:08:10.130 --> 00:08:12.560
I... You...

00:08:20.360 --> 00:08:21.140
Wait!

00:08:21.310 --> 00:08:22.430
Wait!

00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:31.530
In the handouts, you can read about 
the time machine's basic design.

00:08:31.530 --> 00:08:35.470
I will use this conference as an opportunity 
to discuss the fundamental theory behind it.

00:08:33.720 --> 00:08:36.930
Professor Nakabachi

00:08:37.470 --> 00:08:42.170
The operation notes said that 
you'd be able to identify Makise Kurisu.

00:08:42.170 --> 00:08:43.270
Can you do it?

00:08:43.270 --> 00:08:44.290
Yeah.

00:08:44.290 --> 00:08:47.430
Also, it's dangerous to take her outside.

00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:51.530
If we can't find out who stabbed her,

00:08:54.620 --> 00:08:56.430
The same as with Mayuri?

00:08:56.430 --> 00:08:59.110
Doctor!

00:08:59.110 --> 00:09:00.530
What is it?

00:09:00.530 --> 00:09:02.170
You know exactly what!

00:09:02.170 --> 00:09:04.470
What is this "time machine theory" of yours?

00:09:04.470 --> 00:09:05.780
Kerr Black Holes?

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:06.960
World lines?

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:08.970
You stole all this from John Titor!

00:09:09.660 --> 00:09:12.430
<i>Kurisu will be stabbed right here soon.</i>

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:15.200
<i>Is she really going to be here?</i>

00:09:16.390 --> 00:09:19.790
<i>Wait! Maybe she was stabbed elsewhere 
and brought here.</i>

00:09:19.790 --> 00:09:23.120
<i>Yeah... That's possible!</i>

00:09:28.660 --> 00:09:30.280
<i>Kurisu?</i>

00:09:31.970 --> 00:09:33.930
<i>So, it does happen here.</i>

00:09:35.270 --> 00:09:36.770
<i>What's she reading?</i>

00:09:38.380 --> 00:09:39.890
<i>A time machine?</i>

00:09:40.630 --> 00:09:43.350
<i>Is that why she's the key to changing world lines?</i>

00:09:50.080 --> 00:09:51.530
What do you want?

00:09:51.530 --> 00:09:54.910
Daddy, I wanted you to read this.

00:09:54.910 --> 00:09:55.770
<i>Daddy?</i>

00:09:59.010 --> 00:10:00.640
<i>Professor Nakabachi?</i>

00:10:00.640 --> 00:10:03.690
You contacted me for the first time in seven years.

00:10:03.690 --> 00:10:06.320
You asked me to come to 
your press conference, right?

00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:07.850
That was my inspiration...

00:10:07.850 --> 00:10:11.390
<i>Wait, so Kurisu's dad is...</i>

00:10:08.910 --> 00:10:13.770
So I thought I could use it to theorize a time machine.

00:10:14.550 --> 00:10:17.010
I wanted to hear your theories.

00:10:18.460 --> 00:10:21.020
If this is accepted, you can use it

00:10:21.020 --> 00:10:22.930
to show everyone who kicked you out of academia...

00:10:22.930 --> 00:10:25.100
I wasn't kicked out!

00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:28.570
I got sick of them and left.

00:10:28.570 --> 00:10:30.140
Sorry...

00:10:31.810 --> 00:10:33.580
It's not bad.

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:34.680
Really?

00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:37.110
If you're okay with it,

00:10:37.110 --> 00:10:40.140
I thought we could put both 
our names on the paper.

00:10:40.140 --> 00:10:41.880
Because you inspired me...

00:10:41.880 --> 00:10:43.960
Don't be stupid.

00:10:43.960 --> 00:10:45.080
Leave!

00:10:45.760 --> 00:10:49.020
I'll publish this paper under my name.

00:10:49.430 --> 00:10:50.470
Wait!

00:10:50.470 --> 00:10:52.330
You wouldn't steal it, right, Daddy?

00:10:52.970 --> 00:10:55.680
I thought, no matter what, you'd never do that...

00:10:55.680 --> 00:10:56.270
Shut up!

00:11:00.400 --> 00:11:02.390
How dare you call it stealing!

00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:08.030
Why are you so smart?

00:11:08.030 --> 00:11:11.020
A girl shouldn't be smarter than her father!

00:11:11.450 --> 00:11:15.020
If it weren't for you, I'd have been smart, too!

00:11:15.020 --> 00:11:17.030
If it weren't for you...

00:11:17.030 --> 00:11:17.850
I...

00:11:25.970 --> 00:11:28.030
You're that kid from earlier.

00:11:29.030 --> 00:11:30.870
So that's it?

00:11:31.370 --> 00:11:36.930
You were plotting to ruin 
my conference together, right?

00:11:38.900 --> 00:11:41.220
I see...

00:11:41.800 --> 00:11:43.890
So that's it.

00:11:43.890 --> 00:11:45.650
Daddy!

00:11:45.650 --> 00:11:47.680
<i>I'll protect her!</i>

00:11:50.080 --> 00:11:54.010
How dare you insult me?

00:12:00.770 --> 00:12:02.520
Why, you...

00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:06.970
Stop it, Daddy!

00:12:06.970 --> 00:12:08.350
Please!

00:12:09.140 --> 00:12:12.300
Don't even speak to me!

00:12:11.280 --> 00:12:12.300
Oh no!

00:12:17.390 --> 00:12:19.810
What do you know?

00:12:19.810 --> 00:12:21.700
You don't know how I feel.

00:12:21.700 --> 00:12:24.640
You don't know how I've been humiliated...

00:12:24.640 --> 00:12:26.740
The hell I've been through!

00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:29.250
If it weren't for you...

00:12:29.250 --> 00:12:30.310
Don't...

00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:32.650
If it weren't for you...

00:12:34.300 --> 00:12:36.350
Don't do it!

00:12:44.470 --> 00:12:45.690
Kurisu...

00:12:49.380 --> 00:12:51.770
K-Kurisu!

00:12:54.580 --> 00:12:56.310
Fools.

00:12:56.310 --> 00:12:59.020
This is the perfect end for you.

00:13:02.290 --> 00:13:06.220
I'm sorry for involving you...

00:13:06.220 --> 00:13:07.810
Why?

00:13:07.810 --> 00:13:09.390
Because he's my dad.

00:13:10.800 --> 00:13:13.270
I wanted him to accept me.

00:13:13.270 --> 00:13:14.450
That's all.

00:13:14.450 --> 00:13:15.760
Kurisu...

00:13:18.670 --> 00:13:20.310
I'm scared...

00:13:23.750 --> 00:13:27.470
I... I don't want to die.

00:13:29.060 --> 00:13:31.070
I don't want to die.

00:13:32.150 --> 00:13:33.220
I don't...

00:13:37.070 --> 00:13:38.090
Kurisu...

00:13:40.640 --> 00:13:41.600
Kurisu!

00:13:57.300 --> 00:13:58.720
They're back already!

00:14:01.180 --> 00:14:02.390
Okarin!

00:14:05.530 --> 00:14:07.580
Okarin, that blood...

00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:08.750
It's all right.

00:14:08.750 --> 00:14:10.470
It's not his.

00:14:12.640 --> 00:14:15.810
I was the one who killed Kurisu...

00:14:15.810 --> 00:14:17.590
I was the one who killed Kurisu...

00:14:18.360 --> 00:14:20.290
I was the one who killed Kurisu...

00:14:21.660 --> 00:14:22.560
Okarin?

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:26.790
I know it hurts, but you can't give up yet.

00:14:26.790 --> 00:14:29.550
We have enough fuel to go back once more...

00:14:29.550 --> 00:14:30.520
Shut up!

00:14:31.290 --> 00:14:32.970
It'll just be the same!

00:14:33.770 --> 00:14:37.390
The Attractor Field convergence will 
kill her all over again.

00:14:41.300 --> 00:14:42.680
It's your phone.

00:14:42.680 --> 00:14:44.210
A message?

00:14:44.210 --> 00:14:45.280
Open it.

00:14:45.280 --> 00:14:45.870
But...

00:14:45.870 --> 00:14:47.140
Just do it.

00:14:49.290 --> 00:14:52.310
Turn on the TV.

00:14:50.220 --> 00:14:52.310
Turn on the TV?

00:14:52.310 --> 00:14:53.830
The TV?

00:14:56.950 --> 00:15:04.680
Mysterious Fire in Cargo Bay 
Professor Nakabachi Defects to Russia

00:14:57.320 --> 00:15:01.590
The plane carrying Professor Nakabachi 
made it to Russia,

00:15:01.590 --> 00:15:05.040
despite a mysterious cargo bay fire.

00:15:05.040 --> 00:15:07.210
We were very fortunate.

00:15:07.210 --> 00:15:09.860
If this hadn't triggered the metal detector,

00:15:09.660 --> 00:15:12.180
Mayushii

00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:12.180
the paper would have gone up.

00:15:13.450 --> 00:15:15.790
That's Mayushii's metal Upa!

00:15:15.790 --> 00:15:19.610
Look. It has Mayushii's name on it!

00:15:19.610 --> 00:15:20.900
She's right.

00:15:20.900 --> 00:15:23.110
But what's it doing in Russia?

00:15:23.110 --> 00:15:25.970
That paper is the start of everything.

00:15:27.050 --> 00:15:32.600
Next comes the international, 
time machine arms race.

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:37.870
To rule time is to rule the world.

00:15:37.870 --> 00:15:40.810
And that begins a world war.

00:15:43.300 --> 00:15:46.400
5.7 billion lives are at stake.

00:15:46.400 --> 00:15:50.670
Save Makise Kurisu, and change this world line!

00:15:50.670 --> 00:15:51.950
It's impossible...

00:15:52.910 --> 00:15:54.810
It's just like with Mayuri.

00:15:55.860 --> 00:15:58.390
No matter what I do, it'll end up the same.

00:15:59.320 --> 00:16:00.960
Kurisu will die.

00:16:00.960 --> 00:16:03.350
How can you say that after only one time?

00:16:03.350 --> 00:16:04.350
One time?!

00:16:05.010 --> 00:16:06.410
It's more than that...

00:16:06.910 --> 00:16:08.450
How many times...

00:16:08.450 --> 00:16:11.530
How many times do you think I've failed?!

00:16:12.530 --> 00:16:14.350
I can tell...

00:16:14.350 --> 00:16:18.690
How insane this time loop is...

00:16:18.690 --> 00:16:21.780
What a cruel fate it has in store...

00:16:23.810 --> 00:16:25.530
I knew this...

00:16:26.430 --> 00:16:28.350
I knew this would happen.

00:16:28.350 --> 00:16:29.690
I'm tired.

00:16:31.520 --> 00:16:34.750
I'm so tired...

00:16:40.590 --> 00:16:43.770
You're not the kind of person to quit halfway.

00:16:43.770 --> 00:16:45.600
Mayushii knows this!

00:16:46.070 --> 00:16:49.270
You're not the kind of person to ever give up.

00:16:49.270 --> 00:16:53.110
Even when Mayushii couldn't 
say goodbye to her grandmother,

00:16:53.110 --> 00:16:56.810
you never stopped going to her grave.

00:16:56.810 --> 00:16:59.110
That's why I could say goodbye.

00:16:59.930 --> 00:17:02.060
That's why I got better!

00:17:03.880 --> 00:17:06.810
So don't give up.

00:17:11.100 --> 00:17:15.330
You should have received a video file on July 28th.

00:17:19.510 --> 00:17:22.320
<i>July 28th...</i>

00:17:22.320 --> 00:17:23.600
You should be able to watch it,

00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:27.370
now that you've failed once 
to rescue Makise Kurisu.

00:17:28.380 --> 00:17:29.750
What do you mean?

00:17:29.750 --> 00:17:31.280
I'm sorry I lied to you.

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:33.890
The plan called for you to fail once.

00:17:34.620 --> 00:17:36.600
So that you would see this.

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:43.930
What is this?

00:17:43.930 --> 00:17:47.390
Nice to meet you, myself fifteen years ago.

00:17:48.340 --> 00:17:49.860
It's Okarin!

00:17:51.410 --> 00:17:54.380
If you've opened this message,

00:17:54.380 --> 00:17:57.730
then you've failed to rescue Kurisu.

00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:00.310
It must have been painful.

00:18:01.130 --> 00:18:05.610
But that pain gave rise to my obsession.

00:18:05.610 --> 00:18:09.540
So it had to happen.

00:18:10.310 --> 00:18:13.180
You might say it was a part of the preparation.

00:18:14.140 --> 00:18:17.350
Now we can begin the plan for real.

00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:19.710
The plan to save Makise Kurisu,

00:18:19.710 --> 00:18:21.760
and enter Steins Gate.

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:24.020
We have two objectives.

00:18:24.020 --> 00:18:29.320
First, to destroy the paper on time machines,

00:18:29.320 --> 00:18:31.810
which Professor Nakabachi took to Russia.

00:18:32.710 --> 00:18:36.020
Second, to save Makise Kurisu.

00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:37.670
If I could do that...

00:18:37.670 --> 00:18:43.040
But avoiding her death and 
changing the past are impossible

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:46.020
because of the Attractor Field convergence.

00:18:46.020 --> 00:18:47.220
Right?

00:18:47.220 --> 00:18:49.190
I'll be as clear as possible.

00:18:49.190 --> 00:18:50.930
Saving Makise Kurisu is possible.

00:18:51.770 --> 00:18:53.890
You're just approaching it the wrong way.

00:18:54.880 --> 00:18:56.710
Listen well.

00:18:56.710 --> 00:18:59.060
You must not change the past, 
once it's been established.

00:18:59.540 --> 00:19:03.520
You must not undo what you saw that day.

00:19:04.420 --> 00:19:08.810
If you do either, the past will change, 
and all will be lost.

00:19:10.590 --> 00:19:13.770
Remember your experiences 
in the alpha world line.

00:19:14.270 --> 00:19:16.430
It was only three weeks,

00:19:16.430 --> 00:19:20.030
but you should have memories 
of your time with Makise Kurisu.

00:19:20.770 --> 00:19:25.770
Of all you and she sacrificed to save Mayuri.

00:19:26.520 --> 00:19:30.180
Of everything that happened.

00:19:31.530 --> 00:19:36.980
You must not waste those three weeks.

00:19:37.620 --> 00:19:39.390
You must not undo them.

00:19:40.350 --> 00:19:43.740
The only reason you wish so desperately to save her

00:19:43.740 --> 00:19:47.000
is because of the world lines you experienced.

00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:49.780
And it's the sole reason

00:19:49.780 --> 00:19:52.060
I devoted my life to developing a time machine.

00:19:52.770 --> 00:19:55.850
The reason you've managed to get

00:19:55.850 --> 00:19:59.520
as far as you have is that 
we both want to save Kurisu.

00:20:00.290 --> 00:20:03.560
So you must deceive your other self.

00:20:05.170 --> 00:20:08.840
Save her without changing the past where she died.

00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:10.750
Make your past self

00:20:10.750 --> 00:20:13.340
mistake a living Kurisu for a dead one.

00:20:13.760 --> 00:20:17.080
If you do, the past won't change.

00:20:17.600 --> 00:20:18.850
I get it...

00:20:19.260 --> 00:20:20.780
What does he mean?

00:20:20.780 --> 00:20:22.170
Okarin, do you know?

00:20:22.170 --> 00:20:23.470
I know you'll understand me.

00:20:24.150 --> 00:20:28.900
By the way, the time machine's ID is C204.

00:20:28.900 --> 00:20:32.680
I'm sure you know what that stands for.

00:20:32.680 --> 00:20:34.180
Christina...

00:20:34.670 --> 00:20:39.800
And I was the one who named 
the target world line Steins Gate.

00:20:40.530 --> 00:20:44.180
You know why I named it that.

00:20:45.390 --> 00:20:47.220
It doesn't really mean anything.

00:20:48.520 --> 00:20:49.490
Right?

00:20:52.270 --> 00:20:54.080
I will now explain the parameters

00:20:54.810 --> 00:20:57.100
of the final mission, Operation Skuld.

00:20:57.100 --> 00:21:00.790
Change the result without changing 
the established past.

00:21:01.670 --> 00:21:04.340
The past consists of Makise Kurisu, 
lying in a bloody pool,

00:21:04.340 --> 00:21:07.100
and Okabe Rintarou seeing her there.

00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:10.460
Change the past without changing that.

00:21:11.540 --> 00:21:13.680
Deceive your other self.

00:21:13.680 --> 00:21:15.600
Deceive the world.

00:21:16.120 --> 00:21:20.750
That is what you must do to reach Steins Gate.

00:21:22.860 --> 00:21:24.800
Good luck.

00:21:24.800 --> 00:21:27.850
El Psy Congroo.

00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:31.970
What was that?

00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:35.220
Was that you, fifteen years from now?

00:21:35.220 --> 00:21:37.550
The voice was so deep!

00:21:45.460 --> 00:21:47.630
Operation Skuld?

00:21:47.630 --> 00:21:49.890
El Psy Congroo?

00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:53.820
I still talk like that when I'm thirty-three years old?

00:21:55.620 --> 00:21:58.920
I sound like an otaku who's read 
too many bad light novels.

00:21:59.760 --> 00:22:00.930
Okarin?

00:22:01.590 --> 00:22:03.060
I'll do it.

00:22:04.190 --> 00:22:07.430
If that is the choice of Steins Gate.

00:22:08.290 --> 00:22:13.180
I am the mad scientist, Hououin Kyouma!

00:22:13.180 --> 00:22:16.600
Deceiving the world is nothing to me!

00:22:21.050 --> 00:22:23.380
He's back to the usual Okarin.

00:22:23.380 --> 00:22:27.930
But Mayushii likes Okarin better 
when he's like this.

00:22:28.580 --> 00:22:30.810
I'll say it once more.

00:22:30.810 --> 00:22:38.590
I am the mad scientist, Hououin Kyouma...

00:22:40.970 --> 00:22:44.640
And the world is in the palm of my hand!

00:22:45.305 --> 00:23:45.404
